{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit"]]},"topicSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/infoFileName","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/savedStatesDirectory"],"title":"Type Properties","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Properties"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/delete(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/list(bundle:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/restore(bundle:label:)","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/save(bundle:label:)"],"title":"Type Methods","generated":true,"anchor":"Type-Methods"}],"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Manages disk-level snapshots for virtual machine bundles.","type":"text"}],"metadata":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"enum"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotManager"}],"title":"SnapshotManager","roleHeading":"Enumeration","role":"symbol","symbolKind":"enum","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"externalID":"s:15SpooktacularKit15SnapshotManagerO"},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager"},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager"]}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"generated":true,"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError"],"title":"Snapshots","anchor":"Snapshots"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SnapshotManager","kind":"identifier"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"SnapshotManager","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" provides save, restore, list, and delete"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"operations for VM snapshots. Each snapshot is a full copy of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the VM’s disk image ("},{"code":"disk.img","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":") and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"(","type":"text"},{"code":"auxiliary.bin","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"), stored in a named subdirectory under the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"bundle’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"SavedStates\/","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" directory.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"How Snapshots Work","anchor":"How-Snapshots-Work"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Unlike VZ state save (which captures in-memory VM state and","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"requires the VM to be running in the same process),","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"disk-level snapshots copy the on-disk artifacts. This means:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The VM ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"must be stopped"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":" before saving or restoring.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Snapshots work across processes and reboots.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Restoring replaces the current disk and auxiliary storage","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with the snapshot copies.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"APFS Copy-on-Write","anchor":"APFS-Copy-on-Write"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"On APFS volumes, both save and restore use ","type":"text"},{"code":"FileManager.copyItem","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":",","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which the system maps to ","type":"text"},{"code":"clonefile(2)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". This produces a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"copy-on-write clone instead of a byte-for-byte copy, making","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"snapshot creation and restoration near-instantaneous regardless","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"of disk image size. Only blocks that diverge after the clone"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"consume additional storage.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Snapshot Directory Layout","anchor":"Snapshot-Directory-Layout"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["my-vm.vm\/","├── disk.img","├── auxiliary.bin","├── ...","└── SavedStates\/","    ├── clean-install\/","    │   ├── disk.img","    │   ├── auxiliary.bin","    │   └── snapshot-info.json","    └── before-xcode\/","        ├── disk.img","        ├── auxiliary.bin","        └── snapshot-info.json"],"syntax":null},{"type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Example","anchor":"Example"},{"type":"codeListing","code":["let bundle = try VirtualMachineBundle.load(from: bundleURL)","","\/\/ Save a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.save(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ List snapshots","let snapshots = try SnapshotManager.list(bundle: bundle)","for snap in snapshots {","    print(\"\\(snap.label): \\(snap.sizeInBytes) bytes\")","}","","\/\/ Restore a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.restore(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")","","\/\/ Delete a snapshot","try SnapshotManager.delete(bundle: bundle, label: \"clean-install\")"],"syntax":"swift"}],"kind":"content"}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotError":{"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"SnapshotError"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotError","title":"SnapshotError","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshoterror","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"enum","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SnapshotError","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An error that occurs during snapshot operations."}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotManager/restore(bundle:label:)":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Restores a VM bundle from a previously saved snapshot."}],"title":"restore(bundle:label:)","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotmanager\/restore(bundle:label:)","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotManager\/restore(bundle:label:)","fragments":[{"text":"static","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"restore","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"bundle","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:15SpooktacularKit20VirtualMachineBundleV","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"VirtualMachineBundle"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"label"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:SS","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"String"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"throws","kind":"keyword"}]},"doc://SpooktacularKit/documentation/SpooktacularKit/SnapshotInfo":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"SnapshotInfo","kind":"identifier"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/SnapshotInfo","title":"SnapshotInfo","type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/spooktacularkit\/snapshotinfo","role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"SnapshotInfo",